        "Divide the desired serving size by the original serving size to get the scale factor, then multiply each ingredient amount by that factor. For example, moving from 4 servings to 10 servings uses a 2.5x multiplier, so 2 cups becomes 5 cups. The calculator does that math for every ingredient line and keeps the original and scaled amounts side by side.",
